caption.description: Specifically for image credits, tooltips, "legal" fine print, or technical helper text.

large.description: Used for lead paragraphs or "TL;DR" sections to provide high prominence and readability at a glance.

medium.description: The primary workhorse for all DFD content, blog articles, and detailed product descriptions.

small.description: Ideal for dense information blocks, bulleted lists, or footer content where space is at a premium.

bold.description: Optimized for buttons, primary navigation links, and prominent tags. High weight and wider spacing ensure accessibility.

small.description: Used for smaller buttons, status chips, or secondary navigation items within components.

shadow-xs.description: Contact state. Use for Input Fields (Sunken), active borders, or pressed states where items feel flush with the surface.

shadow-sm.description: Touch state. Use for clickable interactive elements like Buttons, list items, or small chips that need a subtle lift.

shadow-md.description: Float state. The default elevation for Cards, Panels, and Content Containers. Defines distinct separation from the background

shadow-lg.description: Lift state. Use for Hover interactions on cards, sticky navigation headers, Dropdown menus, or Tooltips

shadow-xl.description: Focus state. Max elevation. Use exclusively for Modals, Dialogs, Lightboxes, and blocking alerts that float above everything else.

space-8.description: Base Unit. Standard padding inside small buttons.

space-10.description: The Root. Useful for strict 10-based alignments.

radius-sm.description: Inputs, small buttons, internal card elements.

radius-md.description: Base Radius. Standard Buttons, Cards, Popovers.

pair-1-heading.description: A quirkier sans-serif that feels machined and technical.

pair-1-alt.description: A code font for IDs, data, or technical labels.

pair-2-heading.description: A beautiful, heavy serif that feels warm and established.

pair-2-body.description: A friendly, rounded sans-serif that is easy on the eyes.

pair-2-alt.description: A soft monospace that doesn't feel robotic.

pair-3-heading.description: A traditional serif optimized for screens.

pair-3-body.description: A humanist sans-serif that pairs well with classic type.

text-size-14.description: Body Small. Dense interfaces or mobile body text.

text-size-18.description: Intro. Lead paragraphs or large buttons.

line-height-none.description: 100%: Used for single-line UI elements like buttons and chips where height is controlled by padding.

line-height-xs.description: 110%: Extremely tight for massive Hero/Display headers to prevent "gaps" between words.

line-height-sm.description: 125%: The "Heading Standard" for H1H3 to keep stacked titles cohesive.

line-height-md.description: 135%: Balanced spacing for smaller headers (H4H5) and secondary UI text.

line-height-lg.description: 150%: The "Body Standard" for optimal reading comfort and accessibility in paragraphs.

xs.description: Tight spacing between icon and text.

sunken.description: Slightly darker cool gray for inputs.

brand-subtle.description: Pale pink wash for selected states.

accent-subtle.description: Pale cyan wash for info callouts.

accent.description: Darkest cyan for readable accent text.

success.description: Deep green for success message text.

inverted.description: White text for use on top of vibrant buttons.

active.description: Pink border for active text fields.

label.description: For button text and small UI tags.

tight.description: Used for the largest titles (Display, H1) to keep letters from feeling "floaty"

heading.description: The standard for most headings (H2, H3) to balance density and readability.

caption.description: Optimal for smaller headers (H4, H5) and metadata where extra vertical space helps clarity.

body.description: The gold standard for multi-line paragraph text to ensure high accessibility.

ui.description: Reserved for single-line elements like buttons where the auto-layout container defines the height.

hover.description: Useful for applying a subtle wash over buttons/list items

stroke-1.description: Hairline. The standard for all UI dividers and inputs.

stroke-2.description: Thick. Used for active states or selected cards.

stroke-4.description: Heavy. Used for high-contrast focus rings.

opacity-10.description: Very subtle (often used for ghost hover backgrounds).

letter-spacing-tighter.description: Display Headers: For H1/H2 over 40px to prevent a "gappy" look.

letter-spacing-tight.description: Standard Headers: For H3/H4 to make them feel compact and "designed."

letter-spacing-base.description: Standard Body: Default for paragraphs to ensure maximum legibility.

letter-spacing-wide.description: Small Labels: For buttons, tags, or small all-caps text.

letter-spacing-wider.description: Technical/Accent: For tiny captions or "Eyebrow" headers
